705103f-a.text:
Jay Street, east side, at, adjoining and north of Concord Street, showing homes being demolished, to make way for new buildings. The Independent Subway passes under ground at this point, and is a boon to property owners in the area.

December 15, 1936.

F. L. Sperr

705105f-b.text:
(1)
Jay Street, east side, north from Cathedral Place, On the right, is the foreground, is seen St. James Roman Catholic Church.
July 5, 1930.
P. L. Sperr

(2)
The same, also looking east on Cathedral Place to Pearl Street. At the right is a small public Park, partially seen which are in almost every neighborhood in Greater New York.
December 15, 1936.
P. L. Sperr

(3)
The same, a close-up of buildings on the north side of the church, showing also a segment of the Sperry building.
December 15, 1936
P. L. Sperr
